cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about training deep networks for semantic image segmentation using only a fraction of annotated images, which is a problem in computer vision (CV). The proposed method uses CycleGAN, which is a popular generative adversarial network (GAN) model, to perform unpaired image style transfer for semi-supervised segmentation. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also introduces a novel approach that enforces cycle consistency to learn a bidirectional mapping between unpaired images and segmentation masks, which adds an unsupervised regularization effect. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multimedia (cs.MM), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
